messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 6/10/2003 7:44:25 PM Eastern Standard Time,
mummy124@... writes:
> Hey Laura, you made the remark about putting meat tenderizer in Ozzy's food
> so Kelly doesn't eat you know what. Will that work and he eats only dry. How
> much do I use and just regular tenderizer.

Thanks

Mary B
Try a little at a time. They hate the smell when it comes out the other end.
Meat Tenderizer is fairly strong so just a little you wont need much, if it
doesn't work add a little more. Yes, it works on dry food and most dogs will eat
it going in. If that doesn't work I think there is something else you can try
it just slips my mind at the moment.

Laura D
